reference.title: ID_ISAR3_EL1, AArch32 Instruction Set Attribute Register 3, EL1
reference.shortdesc: The ID_ISAR3_EL1 provides information about the instruction sets implemented by the core in AArch32.

section.title: Bit field descriptions
section.p: ID_ISAR3_EL1 is a 32-bit register, and is part of the Identification registers functional group.

dd.p: Indicates support for True NOP instructions:

dlentry.dd: True NOP instructions in both the A32 and instruction sets, and additional NOP-compatible hints.

dd.p: Indicates the support for non flag-setting MOV instructions:

dlentry.dd: Support for instruction set encoding T1 of the MOV (register) instruction, copying from a low register to a low register.

dd.p: Indicates the implemented Table Branch instructions in the instruction set.
Indicates the implemented Synchronization Primitive instructions:

ul.li: The CLREX, LDREXB, STREXB, and STREXH instructions.

dd.p: Indicates the implemented Single Instruction Multiple Data () instructions.

ul.li: The SSAT and USAT instructions, and the Q bit in the PSRs.

The PKHBT, PKHTB, QADD16, QADD8, QASX, QSUB16, QSUB8, QSAX, SADD16, SADD8, SASX, SEL, SHADD16, SHADD8, SHASX, SHSUB16, SHSUB8, SHSAX, SSAT16, SSUB16, SSUB8, SSAX, SXTAB16, SXTB16, UADD16, UADD8, UASX, UHADD16, UHADD8, UHASX, UHSUB16, UHSUB8, UHSAX, UQADD16, UQADD8, UQASX, UQSUB16, UQSUB8, UQSAX, USAD8, USADA8, USAT16, USUB16, USUB8, USAX, UXTAB16, UXTB16 instructions, and the GE[3:0] bits in the s.

dlentry.dd: The field relates only to implemented instructions that perform operations on the general-purpose registers. In an implementation that supports Advanced and floating-point instructions, MVFR0, MVFR1, and MVFR2 give information about the implemented instructions.
The QADD, QDADD, QDSUB, QSUB Q bit in the s.

dd.p: In an AArch64-only implementation, this register is UNKNOWN.
